        • [ - ] Zoltan - member since 15-Feb-20

          Predictable, dull English style football based on crosses had to give way to world class defense. Such a defense can only be beaten by unpredictable, creative one touch football that mixes up one touch, quick passing game with exploiting shooting opportunities both from a distance and close range. This pairing was a mismatch from the very beginning as Liverpool is playing a dull, boring style of football, which can be easily defended. Liverpool is trying to wear down its opponents by dictating the tempo and constantly bombarding them with crosses, hoping that they would make a mistake. When they run into a world class defense this strategy is useless.
